---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import FounderImage from '../assets/founder.jpeg';

// Define the date clearly so Astro doesn't throw a "received object" error
const publishDate = new Date('2025-03-05');
---

<Layout
	title="About the Founder"
	description="Leading the transition toward equitable campus healthcare in Zimbabwe."
	pubDate={publishDate}
	heroImage={FounderImage}
>
	<p>
		Fadzai Zaranyika is a Computer Science student at Ashesi University, driven by the belief that 
		technology should be healthcare's greatest equalizer. As the founder of 
		<strong>Pouls</strong>, my work centers on using software engineering to solve 
		deeply human problems.
	</p>

	<p>
		Having witnessed the devastating impact of medical stigma firsthand within the Zimbabwean 
		university system, I recognized that the "barrier to care" was psychological 
		as much as it was physical. By designing systems that prioritize user anonymity 
		and data security, we are creating a new standard for student welfare.
	</p>

	<h3>Core Competencies & Recognition</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>System Architecture:</strong> Designing secure, end-to-end encrypted health dashboards for sensitive student data.</li>
		<li><strong>iGEM Silver Medalist:</strong> Recognized for excellence in computational biology and project design on a global stage.</li>
		<li><strong>Ashesi Health Grant:</strong> Awarded for innovative, student-led healthcare solutions in higher education.</li>
		<li><strong>Melton Foundation Fellow:</strong> Collaborating with global innovators to solve UN Sustainable Development Goals.</li>
	</ul>
	
</Layout>